divs: sighting detailsi was driving into waupaca on cth e traveling southbound from the ogdensburg area when i noticed a bright light in the sky to south and a little west. the sky was clear with only bright stars visible to the south and more visible to the north. i pulled over to the shoulder and as i was watching the light, another formed next to it, only lasting for a few seconds. both lights disappeared for approx 5 seconds, reappeared for approx 10 seconds and again disappeared.i did not see them return. the light was a bright orange\yellow color, steady and not moving. i,as well as others in the area, have see similar lights to the south in the past, with as many as a dozen lined up in formation just above the horizon.
